<section id="about">
<h2>What city is this?</h2>
<p>Los Angeles is a large city in California, USA. It is located on the west coast and is one of the most famous cities in the world.</p>
</section>

<section id="history">
<h2>History</h2>
<p>Los Angeles was founded in 1781 by Spanish settlers. Over time, it became a major global city, especially known for the film industry.</p>
</section>

<section id="attractions">
<h2>Famous Places</h2>
<ul>
<li>Hollywood</li>
<li>Santa Monica Pier</li>
<li>Griffith Observatory</li>
<li>Venice Beach</li>
</ul>
<img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/7a/Hollywood_Sign_%28Zuschnitt%29.jpg">
</section>

<section id="economy">
<h2>Economy</h2>
<p>Los Angeles has a strong economy based on entertainment (Hollywood), technology, trade, tourism, and the port industry.</p>
</section>

<section id="lifestyle">
<h2>Lifestyle & Culture</h2>
<p>The city is very diverse. People from many cultures live in Los Angeles. It is known for movies, music, fashion, and a relaxed lifestyle.</p>
</section>

<section id="facts">
<h2>Interesting Facts</h2>
<ul>
<li>Over 3.8 million people live in the city</li>
<li>It is the second largest city in the USA</li>
<li>It has more than 300 sunny days per year</li>
</ul>
</section>

<section id="problem">
<h2>Problem: Homelessness</h2>
<p>Los Angeles has a serious homelessness problem. Many people live on the streets due to high rent and social inequality.</p>

<h3>Example Data (estimated)</h3>
